<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397>
    dc:creator "Vargas, Hector A." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A new distribution record, first host plant record and DNA barcoding of the Neotropical micromoth Astrotischeria karsholti Puplesis & Diskus (Lepidoptera, Tischeriidae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "115397" ;
    bibo:journal "Biodiversity Data Journal" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-19" ;
    bibo:startPage "115397" ;
    bibo:volume "11" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure4> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Male adult of Astrotischeria karsholti Puplesis & Diskus, 2003 reared from a leaf mine on Ambrosia cumanensis Kunth (Asteraceae) collected in northern Chile. A Habitus, dorsal view; B Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars 1 and 0.01 mm, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/928924" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Geographic distribution of Astrotischeria karsholti Puplesis & Diskus, 2003 in South America. Previous records from central Peru indicated by square (type locality) and circles, new record from northern Chile indicated by triangle." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/928925" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Natural history of Astrotischeria karsholti Puplesis & Diskus, 2003 in the Azapa Valley, Arica Province of northern Chile. A The host plant Ambrosia cumanensis Kunth (Asteraceae) in the neighbourhood of a citrus orchard; B, C Leaf mine on A. cumanensis previous to nidus formation, adaxial and abaxial views, respectively; D, E Leaf mine at the beginning and at the end of nidus formation, respectively, abaxial view; F Last instar larva removed from mine of B and C; G Nidus of D and E opened to show the pupa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/928926" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.11.e115397.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Maximum Likelihood tree of Astrotischeria karsholti Puplesis & Diskus, 2003 and other members of Tischeriidae, based on mitochondrial DNA sequences. Rectangle indicates a monophyletic group of Astrotischeria Puplesis & Diskus, 2003; species of this genus clustered outside this clade are indicated by black arrows; type species are in bold. Numbers indicate SH-aLRT / UFBoot values (1000 replicates)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/928927" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

